# Cloudflare Pages redirects — ASAP Pest & Wildlife
# 301 redirect map: legacy Webflow site -> new site. Authored 2026-05-25.
# Preserves SEO equity when removeasap.com cuts over to Cloudflare Pages.
#
# The new site is a verbatim URL clone of the old Webflow site: every old page path
# (e.g. /about, /wildlife/armadillo) exists at the same path on the new site and is
# normalized to its trailing-slash canonical automatically by the platform (permanent
# redirect, equity-preserving) — so per-page slash redirects are intentionally NOT listed.
# Only genuinely changed / removed / legacy paths need explicit 301s below.
# Old URL inventory: removeasap.com/sitemap.xml + Wayback Machine (2026-05-25).

# Force www -> apex (activates once www.removeasap.com is attached at cutover)
https://www.removeasap.com/*   https://removeasap.com/:splat   301

# Funnel legacy path
/home   /   301
/book   /contact/   301
/book/  /contact/   301

# Pre-Webflow legacy URLs (old .asp/.htm era) -> nearest current page
/default.asp    /                   301
/about.htm      /about/             301
/contact.asp    /contact/           301
/privacy.htm    /privacy-policy/    301
/news.htm       /blog/              301

# Removed wildlife slug (legacy-domain parity) -> wildlife hub
/wildlife/ground-hog   /wildlife/   301

# Legacy alias domain -> canonical. Same path structure, so :splat carries the path.
# ACTIVATES ONLY once wildliferemovalasap.com (+ www) is attached to this Pages project
# and its DNS is pointed here. Confirm client still owns the alias before relying on this.
https://wildliferemovalasap.com/*       https://removeasap.com/:splat   301
https://www.wildliferemovalasap.com/*   https://removeasap.com/:splat   301
